{"article_id":"vFwWeM0Ixy0IYFJV","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"More than half of Americans support Obamacare ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"according to a Gallup poll","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"taken amid floundering Republican efforts","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"to scrap the law","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"after seven years of promising a replacement .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"The pollsters said","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"55 percent now approve of the Affordable Care Act ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"compared to just 42 percent right after the election .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"It is the first time that Gallup found majority support for the law","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"since it started asking about it in 2012 .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"People of every political affiliation were more likely to support the law than in November ,","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"driven in large part by independents ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"who ' ve increased their support by 17 percentage points","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"compared to 10 each for Republicans and Democrats .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"However , only a quarter of Americans want to keep Obamacare","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"as it is .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"About 40 percent want to reform the law ,","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"while 30 percent want to repeal","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"and replace it .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"Obamacare has consistently split public opinion","depth":5},{"id":20,"text":"since Democrats muscled it to passage in 2010","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"without a single Republican vote ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"with many polls tilting to the negative side .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"In general , Americans tend to like its insurance guarantees and benefits","depth":5},{"id":24,"text":"but despise the individual mandate","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"requiring people to hold insurance or pay a tax .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Yet approval ratings have ticked upward of late ,","depth":4},{"id":27,"text":"as Republicans","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"who control Congress and the White House","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"fail to rally around a replacement plan","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"that can satisfy disparate wings of their own party .","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"\" Trump vehemently attacked the Affordable Care Act during his presidential campaign","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"- and in the days","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"immediately following his election ,","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"the public appeared to agree with him , \"","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"Gallup said .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"\" However , in the five months since ,","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"as Republicans ' efforts","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"to replace the law with one of their own","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"have failed to get off the ground ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"enough Americans have changed their minds about the ACA","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"to create a majority","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"favoring it for the first time . \"","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"House Republicans are trying to revive talks on health reform ,","depth":3},{"id":44,"text":"though Speaker Paul D. Ryan says","depth":4},{"id":45,"text":"the discussions are in the \" conceptual \" phase .","depth":4},{"id":46,"text":"Members of the House Freedom Caucus","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"who blasted the first bill as \" Obamacare lite \"","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"are reviewing a White House idea","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"that would let states apply for a waiver from Obamacare insurance regulations","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"that have been blamed for making coverage more expensive for healthier people .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"The waivers would eliminate parts of Obamacare","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"requiring a minimum set of benefits in plans","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"and a provision","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"known as \" community rating , \"","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"which requires insurers to charge the same amount to people","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"who are the same age","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"and live in the same area .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"No one ' s produced legislative text , however ,","depth":5},{"id":59,"text":"and the proposal could alienate moderates","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"who fear","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"the proposed changes would allow insurers to charge sick people exorbitantly higher prices than healthy ones ,","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"even if insurers couldn ' t technically deny those with pre-existing conditions .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"The House GOP ' s own website says","depth":5},{"id":64,"text":"Americans \" should never be denied coverage","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"or charged more","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"because of a pre-existing condition . \"","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":133,"left":109,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":109,"left":85,"right":108,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":85,"left":76,"right":84,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":76,"left":71,"right":75,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":71,"left":0,"right":70,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":70,"left":1,"right":69,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":69,"left":68,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":68,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":75,"left":73,"right":74,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":73,"left":5,"right":72,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":72,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":74,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":84,"left":79,"right":83,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":79,"left":10,"right":78,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":78,"left"